snippet: An appellate court in Chicago ruled Tuesday that transcripts of F.B.I. wiretaps not played at former Gov. Rod Blagojevich’s corruption trials should remain sealed, at least for now.
abstract: Appellate court in Chicago rules that transcripts of Federal Bureau of Investigation wiretaps not played at former Gov Rod Blagojevich’s corruption trials should remain sealed.
lead_paragraph: An appellate court in Chicago ruled Tuesday that transcripts of F.B.I. wiretaps not played at former Gov. Rod Blagojevich’s corruption trials should remain sealed, at least for now.
